attributes.Long form description: The student is disassembling a wheeled cart. They unscrew the wheels, then the brackets holding the trays in place, then the side bars. Finally, they split the base frame in two.

attributes.Transcription: In front of you, you'll see a bathroom cabinet from IKEA.
Your task for now will be please to disassemble it.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the four wheels.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student tries to grab the wrench but fails to grasp it firmly, so it doesn't go up along with the hand.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the left bracket of the middle tray.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student tries to unscrew a hexagon cap nut but fails to grasp it properly so the wrench slips out.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the right bracket of the middle tray.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student tries to insert the wrench into the hexagon cap nut to unscrew it but fails to grasp it properly.
